00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:02.780
- ...limitations and recommending

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:06.487
tightening up the window that you eat in.

00:00:06.487 --> 00:00:08.180
Now that is a real window,

00:00:08.180 --> 00:00:11.083
whereas the anabolic
window is not a real thing.

00:00:14.152 --> 00:00:18.107
A lot of these people did
P90X, or some other program,

00:00:18.950 --> 00:00:21.170
where they believed that

00:00:22.860 --> 00:00:24.500
you exercise,

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:27.160
and then if you eat something
right after you exercise,

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:28.763
it becomes muscle.

00:00:31.550 --> 00:00:33.420
So, we're going to talk about that today

00:00:33.420 --> 00:00:35.320
and I'm going to answer some questions

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.330
that are more specific towards this,

00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:44.740
and we kind of go outside
of the scope of that

00:00:45.830 --> 00:00:46.663
afterward,

00:00:46.663 --> 00:00:51.470
but I really want to stay
focused on meal timing

00:00:51.470 --> 00:00:55.070
is definitely the theme of what we have

00:00:55.070 --> 00:00:59.660
in the X3 programming for nutrition.

00:00:59.660 --> 00:01:01.223
Also, keep in mind,

00:01:02.210 --> 00:01:06.300
the reason I designed
that program the way I did

00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:10.030
was to keep it really user friendly.

00:01:10.030 --> 00:01:14.480
Like 90% of the people who look at that,

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:16.970
they go, "Okay, I canprobably
take sugar out of my diet,"

00:01:16.970 --> 00:01:20.587
or, "Okay, I can stop drinking Coca-Cola.

00:01:20.587 --> 00:01:21.567
"It's not going to kill me

00:01:21.567 --> 00:01:23.507
"to not go with Coca-Cola anymore."

00:01:27.463 --> 00:01:29.930
So, there's different levels of aggression

00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:33.600
when it comes to choosing
your nutrition program.

00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:35.840
For example when it comes to meal time,

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:38.520
which is what we're talking about today,

00:01:38.520 --> 00:01:42.180
you can have one meal a day

00:01:42.180 --> 00:01:45.400
and get all your nutrition
rammed into that one meal.

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:46.512
That's kind of hard,

00:01:46.512 --> 00:01:49.343
you're eating a lot in a
very short period of time,

00:01:51.474 --> 00:01:54.163
especially if you're
trying to gain muscle.

00:01:55.960 --> 00:01:58.313
When you do that sort of thing,

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:02.027
that makes for a rough 24 hour period,

00:02:02.027 --> 00:02:04.330
especially if you're not ketogenic,

00:02:04.330 --> 00:02:05.430
you're not fat adapted,

00:02:05.430 --> 00:02:10.130
that's a miserable day if
you go 24 hours with no food.

00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.370
Now, if you are fat adapted,

00:02:11.370 --> 00:02:12.520
it's a pretty easy day,

00:02:14.020 --> 00:02:16.850
but, again, these are
different levels of aggression.

00:02:16.850 --> 00:02:20.880
And I will be dealing more in the next,

00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:24.710
probably, four to six months on nutrition

00:02:24.710 --> 00:02:27.870
because I realized there is so much

00:02:27.870 --> 00:02:32.137
crap information out there.

00:02:32.137 --> 00:02:36.790
I hesitate to even call
it nutritional advice

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:41.150
because that denotes some
implication of health,

00:02:41.150 --> 00:02:44.320
however science can't even really decide

00:02:45.407 --> 00:02:46.440
if eating meat will kill you

00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:49.200
or if it will make you
like super fantastic

00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:51.720
and live for longer,

00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:53.180
or if it doesn't matter.

00:02:53.180 --> 00:02:57.700
So, there is absolutely
conflicting evidence.

00:02:57.700 --> 00:03:01.957
I almost say to somebody when they say,

00:03:01.957 --> 00:03:02.817
"Well, let me tell you

00:03:02.817 --> 00:03:04.910
"about my health
observations on nurtition,"

00:03:04.910 --> 00:03:06.860
I go, "I'm going to stop you right there,"

00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:11.573
because health and nutrition,

00:03:12.510 --> 00:03:14.660
you can't really give
a health recommendation

00:03:14.660 --> 00:03:16.860
based on a lot of the
nutrition information

00:03:16.860 --> 00:03:17.708
that's out there,

00:03:17.708 --> 00:03:18.650
because there's so much conflicting,

00:03:18.650 --> 00:03:19.740
there's so much bias,

00:03:19.740 --> 00:03:23.210
and there are companies that make products

00:03:23.210 --> 00:03:27.480
that are processed, usually,
simple carbohydrates,

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:29.940
and they're hell bent on proving

00:03:29.940 --> 00:03:31.963
that those things are healthy.

00:03:32.990 --> 00:03:35.770
That's where most of nutrition
research funding comes from.

00:03:35.770 --> 00:03:37.920
So, you got to keep
all that stuff in mind.

00:03:38.780 --> 00:03:41.350
Now, back to the main topic,

00:03:41.350 --> 00:03:44.180
which is the anabolic window.

00:03:44.180 --> 00:03:46.990
You will walk into just about any gym

00:03:50.388 --> 00:03:53.673
and, aside from the smell
of sweat and mildew,

00:03:56.790 --> 00:03:58.810
you will probably notice,

00:03:58.810 --> 00:04:01.290
the second thing you notice,
other than the smell,

00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:06.290
is the fact that there's a
lot of guys walking around

00:04:06.630 --> 00:04:08.630
looking like they're
holding like a baby bottle

00:04:08.630 --> 00:04:10.200
with like a nipple on top of it,

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:11.870
and it's some sort of mixing cup

00:04:11.870 --> 00:04:14.380
for some sort of protein drink,

00:04:14.380 --> 00:04:15.760
because they got to get their nutrition

00:04:15.760 --> 00:04:19.480
right in that anabolic window.

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:22.753
What's so funny about that is since 2013,

00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:25.510
a couple chaps I've met

00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:32.680
published a literature review.

00:04:33.470 --> 00:04:36.363
They looked at 85 different studies:

00:04:38.370 --> 00:04:39.610
nutrient timing.

00:04:39.610 --> 00:04:42.500
I wrote 85 there to
remind myself to mention

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:46.527
there were 85 different
studies considered in this.

00:04:46.527 --> 00:04:50.430
Is there are a post
exercise anabolic window?

00:04:50.430 --> 00:04:54.600
And these are two guys, two PhDs,

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:59.600
Alan Aragon and Brad Schofield.

00:05:01.503 --> 00:05:03.050
I think I met them at the

00:05:03.050 --> 00:05:07.520
American College of Sports
Medicine Annual Congress.

00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:12.010
So, they considered all
of these different papers

00:05:12.010 --> 00:05:13.250
and they looked at different papers

00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:18.220
who looked at having a high
carbohydrate after your workout

00:05:18.220 --> 00:05:21.450
versus no meal after your workout,

00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:25.313
a high protein meal after your workout,

00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:29.620
really refined sports nutrition drinks

00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:30.580
right after your workout,

00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:32.870
and then comparing that to control groups,

00:05:32.870 --> 00:05:34.870
who basically just had
the same kind of nutrition

00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:37.040
they've always had, or even fasted,

00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:39.583
and then ate at towards
the end of the day.

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:43.430
So, guess what happened?

00:05:43.430 --> 00:05:44.978
Nothing.

00:05:44.978 --> 00:05:48.650
Everybody pretty much grew
the same amount of muscle

00:05:49.799 --> 00:05:52.118
no matter what they did.

00:05:52.118 --> 00:05:56.030
Now, what they don't really
have a lot of data on

00:05:56.030 --> 00:05:59.890
is muscle gains with multi-day fasting

00:06:00.765 --> 00:06:04.140
and I think the reason there's
not enough literature on that

00:06:04.140 --> 00:06:07.920
is because people are typically
doing multi-day fasting

00:06:07.920 --> 00:06:10.530
are either going after cancer

00:06:10.530 --> 00:06:12.490
or they're going after

00:06:14.170 --> 00:06:16.970
really, really aggressive body fat loss,

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:18.610
so those are kind of conflicting goals.

00:06:18.610 --> 00:06:20.340
It's not like somebody
who's morbidly obese

00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:23.334
is like, "Well, I don't want
to lose my pectoral mass."

00:06:23.334 --> 00:06:25.720
They need to lose a lot of fat mass

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:30.720
because it's contributing to
their short life, potentially.

00:06:31.690 --> 00:06:34.890
So, just not a lot of data on that,

00:06:34.890 --> 00:06:37.260
though there are a couple indicators

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:42.220
that show that you can
definitely protect muscle

00:06:42.220 --> 00:06:44.200
with the proper engagement,

00:06:44.200 --> 00:06:47.556
and, we've talked about,
through stabilization firing

00:06:47.556 --> 00:06:51.370
and loading of the body.

00:06:51.370 --> 00:06:54.970
So, you can go multi-day
fast without losing any mass,

00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:55.803
at all,

00:06:58.150 --> 00:07:02.210
but, also doesn't matter

00:07:02.210 --> 00:07:05.600
when you have your next
meal after you work out.

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:08.420
If you want to exercise in the morning

00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:10.970
and then you're dong the
one meal a day thing,

00:07:10.970 --> 00:07:13.653
and then your one meal
is at 8:00 at night,

00:07:14.493 --> 00:07:16.080
you're doing most of your growth

00:07:16.080 --> 00:07:18.330
when you're sleeping anyway,

00:07:18.330 --> 00:07:20.160
so as long as you keep
engaging the muscle,

00:07:20.160 --> 00:07:21.208
even just lightly,

00:07:21.208 --> 00:07:23.060
your body is really not in the phase

00:07:23.060 --> 00:07:27.030
that protein synthesis is going hard,

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:29.500
and for the most part
the protein synthesis

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:32.350
that needs to be going
during the day is happening,

00:07:32.350 --> 00:07:34.650
and of course ATP, collagen,
and the creatine phosphate

00:07:34.650 --> 00:07:37.070
get replaced on a need basis,

00:07:37.070 --> 00:07:38.663
almost no matter what's there.

00:07:40.848 --> 00:07:44.730
Even if you have zero calories
available to metabolize,

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:49.970
that's when you immediately
go into a ketogenic state,

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:53.490
and you start using ketones

00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:56.210
and gluconeogenesis

00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:58.740
to produce the glucoses required,

00:07:58.740 --> 00:08:00.500
the glucose and insulin combination,

00:08:00.500 --> 00:08:03.810
which then penetrate into the muscle cell

00:08:03.810 --> 00:08:06.210
and become those fuels
that need to be replaced.

00:08:06.210 --> 00:08:08.158
So, it's going to happen no matter what.

00:08:08.158 --> 00:08:12.460
So, that means you're losing
body fat while that's going on

00:08:12.460 --> 00:08:15.580
and you're refueling muscle, no problem.

00:08:15.580 --> 00:08:19.290
And anything where you say
like, "Oh, I'm hyperglycemic,"

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:21.750
or, "My hands get shaky,"
or, "I don't feel good,"

00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:23.847
or skip those meals in which your like,

00:08:23.847 --> 00:08:25.720
"Oh I think I need nutrition,"

00:08:25.720 --> 00:08:28.240
it's 'cause your insulin
sensitivity is awful

00:08:29.420 --> 00:08:32.650
and you're just totally sugar adapted

00:08:32.650 --> 00:08:37.650
and that's not going to
help you going long term.

00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:38.720
Another thing,

00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:42.010
which I know will be one
of the first questions

00:08:42.010 --> 00:08:43.270
that we get,

00:08:43.270 --> 00:08:44.950
so I'll just head that off right now,

00:08:44.950 --> 00:08:49.840
is: am I going to need to be fat adapted?

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:52.880
No, but, if you really want to focus on

00:08:55.350 --> 00:08:57.363
rapid fat loss,

00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:00.529
that just means you're only option,

00:09:00.529 --> 00:09:01.980
if you're not fat adapted,

00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:03.080
is caloric restriction,

00:09:03.080 --> 00:09:04.860
such as eating smaller meals,

00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:06.750
maybe throughout the day.

00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:08.440
I think that's a tougher road to go.

00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:09.513
It works.

00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:14.620
We're starting to simplify things,

00:09:14.620 --> 00:09:16.982
like carbohydrates make you fat

00:09:16.982 --> 00:09:20.250
instead of calories,
calories don't make you fat,

00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:22.000
well that's also too simple,

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.573
both are a little bit too simple.

00:09:27.501 --> 00:09:28.334
You should be afraid of insulin,

00:09:28.334 --> 00:09:31.660
insulin is one of the most
powerful hormones in the body,

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:33.370
however, it's only powerful

00:09:33.370 --> 00:09:35.400
when you have a very tiny amount of it.

00:09:35.400 --> 00:09:37.210
When you have a lot of it

00:09:37.210 --> 00:09:41.730
what was powerful
becomes, basically, toxic.

00:09:41.730 --> 00:09:44.520
So, that's just something to keep in mind.

00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:47.070
And another thing,
another one of my rants,

00:09:47.070 --> 00:09:48.090
which I won't go in now,

00:09:48.090 --> 00:09:50.710
is there's no such thing as a bad hormone,

00:09:50.710 --> 00:09:52.040
cortisol exists for a reason,

00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:53.280
insulin exists for a reason,

00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:58.280
and they're powerful if you
trigger them in the proper way.

